sheEthernetMib.name: sheEthernetMib

revisions.description: New Type SheEtnernetControlRequestResultType defined. Used for ReqResult in control group.
Change Size-values for sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemoteChassis and sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemoteSlot and equivalent controlgroup-values.
Correct typo in flowControl description. Change syntax for ...ControlTimeStamp.
Restrict configuration of sheEthernetPortControlDuplexMode to full only. Add operstate down alarm trap.
Delete not longer needed items: AlarmSeverity and OperStateDown-Alarm. Both will be handled by she-physical-mib.
Correct ranges for sfp-data - could be empty if no sfp is plugged.
Take over by Gerd Barchmann for R2.5.
Take corrections from SHE MIB release 155 for R2.0/R2.3.
Correct usage of predefined type TruthValue.
Add status attributes for SFP diagnostic values. Correct description for sheEthernetPortNegotiationMode.
Modify possible range for Rate configuration.

sheEthernetMib.contactinfo: Gerd Barchmann COO BBA DSLAM RD SDE HW1 +49 3834 555654 gerd.barchmann@nsn.com
sheEthernetMib.description: This MIB contains all ethernet specific configurations and informations. Some statistic counters from the Etherlike MIB are included.

sheEthernetPortEntry.name: sheEthernetPortEntry
sheEthernetPortEntry.description: Each entry represents a physical ethernet interface. Index by ifIndex.

sheEthernetPortType.name: sheEthernetPortType
sheEthernetPortType.description: This value must always be configured. SheEthernetPortType 0 - unknown 1 - electrical 2 - optical Select the type of used interface.

sheEthernetPortTransmissionRate.name: sheEthernetPortTransmissionRate
sheEthernetPortTransmissionRate.description: The speed of port. Unit is Mbit/s. A modification is only useful for electrical-interfaces. Optical-interfaces will always support 1000 MBIT/s.

sheEthernetPortDuplexMode.name: sheEthernetPortDuplexMode
sheEthernetPortDuplexMode.description: The duplex status of port. The SHE will support always full duplex. SheEthernetDuplexType 1 - full 2 - half 3 - notAvailable

sheEthernetPortFlowControl.name: sheEthernetPortFlowControl
sheEthernetPortFlowControl.description: The flow-control mode of port. SheEthernetFlowControlType 0 - notAvailable 1 - disabled 2 - enabledBoth 4 - enabledSymetrical 8 - enabledAsymetrical The Symetrical types are only useful for electrical GE.

sheEthernetPortNegotiationMode.name: sheEthernetPortNegotiationMode
sheEthernetPortNegotiationMode.description: The Auto Negotiation mode of port. Default is auto. Speed will not be part of the autonegotiation. In case of Rate = 1000 and PortType = electrical, the negotiation mode is always auto (default). SheEthernetNegotiationType 1 - auto 2 - force 3 - notAvailable

sheEthernetPortSfpTranseiver.name: sheEthernetPortSfpTranseiver
sheEthernetPortSfpTranseiver.reference: according SFP transceiver MultiSource Agreement (MSA) table 3.1
sheEthernetPortSfpTranseiver.description: Code for electrical or optical compatibility. If 0 (unknown) maybe no SFP module is plugged and the following table values are not valid. For she only optical sfp-modules are allowed. SheEthernetTranseiverType 0 - unknown 1 - electrical (1000-T) 2 - electricalCoaxial(1000-CX) 3 - opticalLongHaul(1000-LX) 4 - opticalShortHaul(1000-SX)

sheEthernetPortSfpVendorName.name: sheEthernetPortSfpVendorName
sheEthernetPortSfpVendorName.reference: according SFP transceiver MultiSource Agreement (MSA) table 3.1

sheEthernetPortSfpVendorPartNumber.name: sheEthernetPortSfpVendorPartNumber
sheEthernetPortSfpVendorPartNumber.reference: according SFP transceiver MultiSource Agreement (MSA) table 3.1
sheEthernetPortSfpVendorPartNumber.description: Part number provided by SFP transeiver vendor (ASCII). 16 Byte.

sheEthernetPortSfpVendorRevision.name: sheEthernetPortSfpVendorRevision
sheEthernetPortSfpVendorRevision.reference: according SFP transceiver MultiSource Agreement (MSA) table 3.1
sheEthernetPortSfpVendorRevision.description: Revision level for part number provided by vendor (ASCII). 4 Byte.

sheEthernetPortSfpVendorSerialNumber.name: sheEthernetPortSfpVendorSerialNumber
sheEthernetPortSfpVendorSerialNumber.reference: according SFP transceiver MultiSource Agreement (MSA) table 3.1
sheEthernetPortSfpVendorSerialNumber.description: Serial number provided by vendor (ASCII). 16 Byte.

sheEthernetPortSfpDateCode.name: sheEthernetPortSfpDateCode
sheEthernetPortSfpDateCode.reference: according SFP transceiver MultiSource Agreement (MSA) table 3.1
sheEthernetPortSfpDateCode.description: Vendor's manufacturing date code (ASCII). 2 Byte low order digit's for year (00=2000) 2 Byte digits of month's (01=Jan ... 12=Dec) 2 Byte day of month's (01..31) 2 Byte vendor specific lot-code, may be blank

sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemoteChassis.name: sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemoteChassis
sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemoteChassis.description: Only used for Link Discovery. Set by operator. No further meaning for the NE. IP Address of the remote NE.

sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemoteSlot.name: sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemoteSlot
sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemoteSlot.description: Only used for Link Discovery. Set by operator. No further meaning for the NE.

sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemotePort.name: sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemotePort
sheEthernetPortPhysicalRemotePort.description: Only used for Link Discovery. Set by operator. No further meaning for the NE.

sheEthernetPortPhysicalLinkDiscoveryMode.name: sheEthernetPortPhysicalLinkDiscoveryMode
sheEthernetPortPhysicalLinkDiscoveryMode.description: Only used for Link Discovery. Set by operator. No further meaning for the NE. Automatic mode is not supported by release 1.0.

sheEthernetPortAlarmSeverityIndex.name: sheEthernetPortAlarmSeverityIndex
sheEthernetPortAlarmSeverityIndex.description: Used alarm severity for this portentry.

sheEthernetPortSwitchoverOnLinkDown.name: sheEthernetPortSwitchoverOnLinkDown
sheEthernetPortSwitchoverOnLinkDown.description: A given port's link status is monitored. When link down for the port is detected, switchover from an active board to a standby board is performed.

sheEthernetPortSfpDiagnosticValid.name: sheEthernetPortSfpDiagnosticValid
sheEthernetPortSfpDiagnosticValid.description: If set, the following corresponding status parameters are valid.

sheEthernetPortSfpTemperature.name: sheEthernetPortSfpTemperature
sheEthernetPortSfpTemperature.description: Internally measured transceiver temperature. Represented as a 16 bit signed twos complement value in increments of 1/256 degrees Celsius, yielding a total range of -128C to +128C. Temperature accuracy is vendor specific but must be better than +/-3 degrees Celsius over specified operating temperature and voltage.The temperature in degrees Celsius is given by the signed twos complement value with LSB equal to 1/256 C. Coding examples: DECIMAL HIGH BYTE LOW BYTE +127.996 7F FF +1.000 01 00 +0.004 00 01 -0.004 FF FF -1.000 FF 00 -127.996 80 01 -128.000 80 00 Only valid if sheEthernetPortSfpDiagnosticValid entry is true.

sheEthernetPortSfpSupplyVoltage.name: sheEthernetPortSfpSupplyVoltage
sheEthernetPortSfpSupplyVoltage.description: Internally measured transceiver supply voltage. Represented as a 16 bit unsigned integer with the voltage defined as the full 16 bit value (0 .. 65535) with LSB equal to 100 uVolt, yielding a total range of 0 to +6.55 Volts. Practical considerations to be defined by transceiver manufacturer will tend to limit the actual bounds of the supply voltage measurement. Accuracy is vendor specific but must be better than +/-3% of the manufacturer's nominal value over specified operating temperature and voltage. Note that in some transceivers, transmitter supply voltage and receiver supply voltage are isolated. In that case, only one supply is monitored. Only valid if sheEthernetPortSfpDiagnosticValid entry is true.

sheEthernetPortSfpLaserBiasCurrent.name: sheEthernetPortSfpLaserBiasCurrent
sheEthernetPortSfpLaserBiasCurrent.description: Measured TX bias current in uA. Represented as a 16 bit unsigned integer with the current defined as the full 16 bit value (0 .. 65535) with LSB equal to 2 uA, yielding a total range of 0 to 131 mA. Accuracy is vendor specific but must be better than +/-10% of the manufacturer's nominal value over specified operating temperature and voltage. Only valid if sheEthernetPortSfpDiagnosticValid entry is true.

sheEthernetPortSfpTxPower.name: sheEthernetPortSfpTxPower
sheEthernetPortSfpTxPower.description: Measured TX output power. Represented as a 16 bit unsigned integer with the power defined as the full 16 bit value (0 .. 65535) with LSB equal to 0.1 uW, yielding a total range of 0 to 6.5535 mW (~ -40 to +8.2 dBm). Data is assumed to be based on measurement of laser monitor photodiode current. It is factory calibrated to absolute units using the most representative fiber output type. Accuracy is vendor specific but must be better than +/-3dB over specified temperature and voltage. Data is not valid when the transmitter is disabled. Only valid if sheEthernetPortSfpDiagnosticValid entry is true.

sheEthernetPortSfpRxPower.name: sheEthernetPortSfpRxPower
sheEthernetPortSfpRxPower.description: Measured RX received optical power. Represented as a 16 bit unsigned integer with the power defined as the full 16 bit value (0 .. 65535) with LSB equal to 0.1 uW, yielding a total range of 0 to 6.5535 mW (~ -40 to +8.2 dBm). Absolute accuracy is dependent upon the exact optical wavelength. For the vendor specified wavelength, accuracy shall be better than +/-3dB over specified temperature and voltage. This accuracy shall be maintained for input power levels up to the lesser of maximum transmitted or maximum received optical power per the appropriate standard. It shall be maintained down to the minimum transmitted power minus cable plant loss (insertion loss or passive loss) per the appropriate standard. Absolute accuracy beyond this minimum required received input optical power range is vendor specific. Only valid if sheEthernetPortSfpDiagnosticValid entry is true.

sheEthernetPortControlIndex.description: The index if the interface to be configured.

sheEthernetPortControlTimer.name: sheEthernetPortControlTimer
sheEthernetPortControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheEthernetPortControlTimestamp.name: sheEthernetPortControlTimestamp
sheEthernetPortControlTimestamp.description: Time stamp attribute set at the end of a command.

sheEthernetPortControlReqResult.name: sheEthernetPortControlReqResult
sheEthernetPortControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheEthernetPortControlType.name: sheEthernetPortControlType
sheEthernetPortControlType.description: Select the type of used interface. SheEthernetPortType 1 - electrical 2 - optical

sheEthernetPortControlRate.name: sheEthernetPortControlRate
sheEthernetPortControlRate.description: Used Datarate. This configuration is only useful for electrical-interfaces. Optical-interfaces will always support 1000 MBIT/s.

sheEthernetPortControlAlarmSeverityIndex.name: sheEthernetPortControlAlarmSeverityIndex
sheEthernetPortControlAlarmSeverityIndex.description: Set alarm severity for this portentry.

sheEthernetPortControlSwitchoverOnLinkDo.name: sheEthernetPortControlSwitchoverOnLinkDown
sheEthernetPortControlSwitchoverOnLinkDo.description: A given port's link status is monitored. When link down for the port is detected, switchover from an active board to a standby board is performed.

sheDot3StatsEntry.name: sheDot3StatsEntry
sheDot3StatsEntry.description: One entry per physical ethernet interface. Index is ifIndex.

sheDot3StatsAlignmentErrors.name: sheDot3StatsAlignmentErrors
sheDot3StatsAlignmentErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the alignmentError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

sheDot3StatsFCSErrors.name: sheDot3StatsFCSErrors
sheDot3StatsFCSErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that are an integral number of octets in length but do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameCheckError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

sheDot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames.name: sheDot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames
sheDot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by exactly one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts, ifOutMulticastPkts, or ifOutBroadcastPkts, and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the dot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames object.

sheDot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames.name: sheDot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames
sheDot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts, ifOutMulticastPkts, or ifOutBroadcastPkts, and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the dot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames object.

sheDot3StatsSQETestErrors.name: sheDot3StatsSQETestErrors
sheDot3StatsSQETestErrors.description: A count of times that the SQE TEST ERROR message is generated by the PLS sublayer for a particular interface. The SQE TEST ERROR message is defined in section 7.2.2.2.4 of ANSI/IEEE 802.3-1985 and its generation is described in section 7.2.4.6 of the same document.

sheDot3StatsDeferredTransmissions.name: sheDot3StatsDeferredTransmissions
sheDot3StatsDeferredTransmissions.description: A count of frames for which the first transmission attempt on a particular interface is delayed because the medium is busy. The count represented by an instance of this object does not include frames involved in collisions.

sheDot3StatsLateCollisions.name: sheDot3StatsLateCollisions
sheDot3StatsLateCollisions.description: The number of times that a collision is detected on a particular interface later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet. Five hundred and twelve bit-times corresponds to 51.2 microseconds on a 10 Mbit/s system. A (late) collision included in a count represented by an instance of this object is also considered as a (generic) collision for purposes of other collision-related statistics.

sheDot3StatsExcessiveCollisions.name: sheDot3StatsExcessiveCollisions
sheDot3StatsExcessiveCollisions.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular interface fails due to excessive collisions.

sheDot3StatsInternalMacTransmitErrors.name: sheDot3StatsInternalMacTransmitErrors
sheDot3StatsInternalMacTransmitErrors.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular interface fails due to an internal MAC sublayer transmit error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the dot3StatsLateCollisions object, the dot3StatsExcessiveCollisions object, or the dot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors object. The precise meaning of the count represented by an instance of this object is implementation- specific. In particular, an instance of this object may represent a count of transmission errors on a particular interface that are not otherwise counted.

sheDot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors.name: sheDot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors
sheDot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors.description: The number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame on a particular interface. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented at most once per transmission attempt, even if the carrier sense condition fluctuates during a transmission attempt.

sheDot3StatsFrameTooLongs.name: sheDot3StatsFrameTooLongs
sheDot3StatsFrameTooLongs.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that exceed the maximum permitted frame size. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameTooLong status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

sheDot3StatsInternalMacReceiveErrors.name: sheDot3StatsInternalMacReceiveErrors
sheDot3StatsInternalMacReceiveErrors.description: A count of frames for which reception on a particular interface fails due to an internal MAC sublayer receive error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the dot3StatsFrameTooLongs object, the dot3StatsAlignmentErrors object, or the dot3StatsFCSErrors object. The precise meaning of the count represented by an instance of this object is implementation- specific. In particular, an instance of this object may represent a count of receive errors on a particular interface that are not otherwise counted.
